projectInfo.name: xmojo
projectInfo.credits: This report contains data retrieved from the National Vulnerability Database: http://nvd.nist.gov

vulnerability.name: CVE-2011-4461
vulnerability.description: Jetty 8.1.0.RC2 and earlier computes hash values for form parameters without restricting the ability to trigger hash collisions predictably, which allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (CPU consumption) by sending many crafted parameters.

reference.name: 20111228 n.runs-SA-2011.004 - web programming languages and platforms - DoS through hash table

vulnerability.name: CVE-2009-1524
vulnerability.cwe: CWE-79 Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')
vulnerability.description: Cross-site scripting (XSS) vulnerability in Mort Bay Jetty before 6.1.17 allows remote attackers to inject arbitrary web script or HTML via a directory listing request containing a ; (semicolon) character.

vulnerability.name: CVE-2009-1523
vulnerability.cwe: CWE-22 Improper Limitation of a Pathname to a Restricted Directory ('Path Traversal')
vulnerability.description: Directory traversal vulnerability in the HTTP server in Mort Bay Jetty 5.1.14, 6.x before 6.1.17, and 7.x through 7.0.0.M2 allows remote attackers to access arbitrary files via directory traversal sequences in the URI.

vulnerability.name: CVE-2007-5615
vulnerability.cwe: CWE-94 Improper Control of Generation of Code ('Code Injection')
vulnerability.description: CRLF injection vulnerability in Mortbay Jetty before 6.1.6rc0 allows remote attackers to inject arbitrary HTTP headers and conduct HTTP response splitting attacks via unspecified vectors.

vulnerability.name: CVE-2007-5614
vulnerability.description: Mortbay Jetty before 6.1.6rc1 does not properly handle "certain quote sequences" in HTML cookie parameters, which allows remote attackers to hijack browser sessions via unspecified vectors.

vulnerability.name: CVE-2007-5613
vulnerability.cwe: CWE-79 Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')
vulnerability.description: Cross-site scripting (XSS) vulnerability in Dump Servlet in Mortbay Jetty before 6.1.6rc1 allows remote attackers to inject arbitrary web script or HTML via unspecified parameters and cookies.

vulnerability.name: CVE-2005-3747
vulnerability.description: Unspecified vulnerability in Jetty before 5.1.6 allows remote attackers to obtain source code of JSP pages, possibly involving requests for .jsp files with URL-encoded backslash ("%5C") characters. NOTE: this might be the same issue as CVE-2006-2758.
